article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 78, Pacific 73
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Kwame Vaughn scored 21 points as Cal State Fullerton ran its winning streak to seven with a 78-73 victory over Pacific on Monday night. D.J. Seeley added 21 points and Omondi Amoke had his fifth double-double with 11 points and 11 rebounds for the Titans (10-3, 2-0 Big West), whose streak is their longest since an eight-gamer in the 1990-91 season. Orane Chin added 13 points and Isiah Umipig 10 for Cal State Fullerton, which shot 54 percent (27 of 50), including 12 of 25 from 3-point range. Lorenzo McCloud's 19 points and eight assists led the Tigers (4-8, 0-1), who lost their fifth straight and fell to 0-7 on the road. Khalil Kelley scored 15 points, and Travis Fulton and Ross Rivera had 12 apiece. Pacific was outrebounded 36-24.
